//
ðŸ§© 5. Constructor Chaining
ðŸ“˜ What It Is:
Constructor Chaining means one constructor calling another constructor
inside the same class using this(), or from parent class using super().

ðŸ’¡ Purpose:
To avoid code duplication and reuse constructor logic.
//
ðŸ§© 6. Constructor vs Method
| Feature         | Constructor                                 | Method                       |
| --------------- | ------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------- |
| **Purpose**     | Initializes an object                       | Performs a task or operation |
| **Name**        | Same as class name                          | Can be any name              |
| **Return Type** | No return type (not even void)              | Must have a return type      |
| **Call**        | Called automatically when object is created | Called manually using object |
| **Inheritance** | Not inherited                               | Can be inherited             |
